s%20a%20parent%2C%20and%20the%20ability%20to%20do%20so%20is%20a%20privilege%20I%20don't%20take%20for%20granted.%20So%20far%2C%20I've%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffamily-has-traveled-the-world-top-destinations-picks-kids-teens-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etaken%20my%20children%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%2026%20countries%20across%20six%20continents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20time%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finternational-travel-kids-stress-free-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etraveling%20with%20my%20kids%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20changed%20the%20way%20I%20parent%2C%20whether%20we're%20at%20home%20or%20thousands%20of%20miles%20away.%20Here%20are%20six%20ways%20traveling%20has%20influenced%20the%20way%20I%20parent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22966f033b-df3b-4f5e-b538-37b4d10f6e5b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20realize%20how%20little%20my%20kids%20actually%20need%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20used%20to%20be%20obsessed%20with%20getting%20my%20children%20the%20right%20type%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-stem-science-based-toys-kids-love-holiday-christmas-gift-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etoys%20to%20promote%20learning%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20development.%20I%20wondered%20if%20they%20had%20enough%20layers%20for%20playing%20in%20the%20snow%20and%20the%20best%20shoes%20for%20climbing%20at%20the%20playground.%20Through%20traveling%2C%20I%20saw%20firsthand%20how%20little%20children%20really%20need%20to%20be%20happy%20and%20thrive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Marrakesh%2C%20my%20son%20played%20soccer%20in%20the%20winding%20streets%20of%20the%20ancient%20medina%20with%20kids%20wearing%20worn%2C%20off-brand%20Crocs.%20They%20barely%20stayed%20on%20their%20feet%2C%20but%20the%20game%20went%20on%2C%20full%20of%20laughter.%20In%20India%2C%20I%20saw%20children%20in%20threadbare%20clothing%20happily%20playing%20with%20no%20special%20toys%20required.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EI%20realized%20that%2C%20despite%20my%20incredible%20fortune%20to%20be%20able%20to%20get%20my%20children%20nearly%20whatever%20I%20wanted%2C%20they%20would%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbuy-name-brand-clothes-for-kids-with-limited-budget-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efine%20with%20the%20basics%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20now%20know%20that%20my%20entire%20family%20is%20better%20off%20free%20from%20the%20pressures%20of%20always%20chasing%20more%20things%20and%20wanting%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2279465c49-174d-493f-a29e-82bb7e683287%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI'm%20not%20as%20hung%20up%20on%20what%20my%20children%20eat%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETravel%20often%20involves%20unexpected%20cultural%20differences%20that%20require%20my%20family%20to%20adapt%20on%20the%20fly%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20food.%20For%20breakfast%20in%20South%20Korea%2C%20we%20found%20ourselves%20with%20bowls%20of%20soup%20rather%20than%20cereal.%20In%20Egypt%2C%20we%20ate%20spaghetti%20mixed%20with%20lentils%2C%20rice%2C%20and%20chickpeas%20instead%20of%20meatballs.%20In%20Japan%2C%20our%20pizza%20came%20topped%20with%20honey.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETraveling%20has%20taught%20me%20that%20many%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmom-went-from-having-three-picky-eaters-to-none-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efood%20rules%3C%2Fa%3E%20I%20once%20accepted%20as%20gospel%20are%20really%20arbitrary%20cultural%20practices.%20I%20no%20longer%20care%20if%20my%20children%20want%20grilled%20cheese%20for%20breakfast.%20If%20they%20want%20to%20experiment%20in%20the%20kitchen%20and%20mix%20items%20that%20don't%20seem%20to%20go%20together%2C%20like%20putting%20jelly%20on%20samosas%2C%20I%20let%20them%20try%20it.%20I%20still%20care%20about%20nutrition%2C%20but%20I'm%20a%20lot%20less%20hung%20up%20on%20what%20they%20eat%20and%20when.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224618%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20author%20poses%20with%20two%20of%20her%20children.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69aae0a21fb3fcb426490aba%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223464%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20says%20that%20traveling%20internationally%20with%20her%20children%20helped%20her%20realize%20that%20her%20kids%20need%20fewer%20things%20to%20be%20content.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Jamie%20Davis%20Smith.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d40b0804-a844-41e3-a445-468cbc52e2d0%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI'm%20more%20flexible%20with%20my%20children%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20used%20to%20be%20hung%20up%20on%20strict%20bedtimes%20and%20mealtimes.%20While%20traveling%2C%20I%20witnessed%20parents%20around%20the%20world%20following%20very%20different%20rules%20than%20I%20did.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Europe%2C%20I%20saw%20children%20out%20to%20dinner%20at%2010%3A00%20at%20night%20with%20even%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmom-letting-kids-sleep-screentime-do-nothing-summer-break-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elater%20bedtimes%3C%2Fa%3E.%20These%20children%20were%20happy%20and%20thriving.%20I%20realized%20that%20the%20sky%20wouldn't%20fall%20if%20I%20allowed%20my%20kids%20to%20stay%20up%20past%20their%20bedtime%20or%20if%20we%20didn't%20eat%20lunch%20exactly%20at%20noon.%20Letting%20go%20of%20strict%20schedules%20has%20been%20incredibly%20freeing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220458f5d0-a028-440f-8a06-2b1dddada66a%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20handle%20stress%20better%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20travel%2C%20changes%20in%20plans%20are%20par%20for%20the%20course.%20Trains%20get%20canceled.%20Attractions%20may%20be%20sold%20out.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworking-mom-kids-hospitalized-on-business-trip-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EKids%20still%20get%20sick%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20even%20far%20from%20home.%20Traveling%20with%20my%20children%20has%20forced%20me%20to%20keep%20a%20level%20head%20as%20I%20navigate%20these%20challenges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20home%2C%20I%20put%20these%20lessons%20into%20practice.%20If%20I%20have%20to%20deal%20with%20a%20last-minute%20change%20in%20plans%20because%20my%20son%20gets%20the%20flu%20or%20a%20playdate%20is%20called%20off%2C%20it's%20no%20longer%20a%20big%20deal.%20When%20I%20am%20on%20the%20verge%20of%20panic%2C%20I%20remember%20the%20time%20I%20discovered%20the%20train%20I%20had%20planned%20on%20taking%20out%20of%20Venice%20wasn't%20running.%20It%20could%20have%20been%20a%20catastrophe%2C%20but%20with%20some%20creative%20thinking%2C%20I%20got%20us%20to%20our%20next%20destination%20on%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%2C%20I%20was%20told%20(incorrectly)%20that%20my%20son%20needed%20emergency%20surgery%20in%20Jamaica.%20I%20had%20to%20make%20sure%20he%20was%20well%20cared%20for%20in%20a%20country%20with%20a%20vastly%20different%20medical%20system%20than%20the%20one%20I%20am%20used%20to.%20He%20recovered%20in%20a%20couple%20of%20days%20with%20minimal%20intervention.%20Having%20the%20experience%20of%20navigating%20complex%20issues%20in%20countries%20where%20I%20don't%20speak%20the%20language%20and%20must%20deal%20with%20cultural%20and%20administrative%20differences%20makes%20everyday%20problems%20easier%20to%20handle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20author's%20children%20hike%20along%20the%20water.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69aae0fbd3e2f1aef36a1ccb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20says%20that%20she's%20learned%20to%20let%20traditional%20schedules%20go%20and%20embrace%20being%20in%20the%20moment.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Jamie%20Davis%20Smith.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cbf7861a-8b7c-44ed-859e-0c82312e4a8e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20make%20more%20time%20for%20fun%20with%20my%20children%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20role%20as%20a%20parent%20is%20often%20purely%20managerial.%20I%20drive%20my%20children%20to%20various%20activities%20and%20pick%20them%20up%20from%20school.%20I%20make%20their%20doctor's%20appointments%20and%20feed%20them%20dinner.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EWhen%20we%20travel%2C%20many%20of%20these%20responsibilities%20vanish.%20My%20children%20and%20I%20spend%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftravel-with-teens-australia-us-mexico-enjoyable-tips-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emore%20time%20having%20fun%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20enjoying%20each%20other's%20company.%20We%20play%20endless%20rounds%20of%20Uno%20and%20laugh%20at%20inside%20jokes.%20It%20can%20be%20challenging%20to%20find%20time%20to%20create%20joy%20amid%20the%20relentless%20pressures%20of%20everyday%20life.%20However%2C%20traveling%20has%20shown%20me%20that%20doing%20so%20is%20essential%20to%20building%20a%20strong%2C%20lasting%20relationship%20with%20them.%20It%20also%20helps%20provide%20moments%20of%20respite%20from%20the%20daily%20grind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2279c99e91-4b88-4ef2-879d-77181816dbe3%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20look%20for%20new%20experiences%20closer%20to%20home%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20it%20were%20up%20to%20me%2C%20I%20would%20travel%20full-time.%20However%2C%20I%20need%20to%20work%2C%20and%20my%20children%20need%20to%20attend%20school%2C%20so%20that's%20not%20feasible.%20Instead%2C%20I%20look%20for%20more%20interesting%20experiences%20closer%20to%20home.%20I've%20learned%20that%20it's%20possible%20to%20experience%20something%20new%20and%20joyful%20just%20about%20anywhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20when%20I%20can't%20travel%2C%20I%20try%20to%20act%20like%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-back-home-after-living-abroad-explored-hometown-like-tourist-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etourist%20in%20my%20hometown%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20seek%20out%20new%20hikes%2C%20