esy%20of%20Paulina%20Roe%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EI%20have%20an%20irregular%20schedule%2C%20so%20I%20always%20struggled%20with%20childcare.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EI%20then%20found%20a%20coworking%20space%20with%20an%20on-site%20preschool%2C%20which%20has%20changed%20everything%20for%20me.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EI%20can%20now%20work%20stress-free%2C%20while%20my%20daughter%20learns%20in%20a%20room%20a%20few%20feet%20from%20me.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wish%20I%20had%20known%20about%20coworking%20spaces%20with%20attached%20childcare%2Fpreschools%20much%20sooner%20in%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstranger-told-something-about-parenting-that-has-stuck-with-me-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eparenting%20journey%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20community%20helped%20me%20solve%20a%20problem%20I%20had%20been%20stressing%20over%20for%20two%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20a%20Chicago%20mom%2C%20an%20on-air%20contributor%20on%20%26quot%3BThe%20Fred%20Show%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20nationally%20syndicated%20morning%20radio%20show%2C%20and%20the%20founder%20of%20The%20Mami%20Collective%2C%20a%20media%20platform%20for%20ambitious%20mothers.%20My%20workdays%20aren't%20traditional%2C%20and%20they%20certainly%20don't%20fit%20into%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-workers-shocked-by-nine-to-five-work-schedule-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E9-5%20schedule%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20mornings%20typically%20start%20at%204%20a.m.%2C%20and%20once%20the%20show%20ends%20at%2010%20a.m.%2C%20the%20rest%20of%20my%20morning%20is%20packed%20with%20meetings%2C%20recordings%2C%20and%20deadlines.%20Once%20that's%20wrapped%20up%2C%20it's%20time%20to%20head%20home%20to%20relieve%20my%20mother-in-law%20or%20sister-in-law%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworking-remotely-childcare-costs-career-growth-return-to-office-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echildcare%20duties%3C%2Fa%3E.%20My%20husband%20is%20a%20fireman%20for%20the%20city%20of%20Chicago%20and%20has%20a%20side%20gig%2C%20so%20I've%20become%20the%20primary%20caretaker%20of%20our%202-year-old%20daughter%20every%20day%20after%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20a%20long%20time%2C%20childcare%20was%20the%20hardest%20piece%20to%20align%20with%20our%20reality.%20But%20when%20I%20came%20across%20a%20day%20care%20and%20preschool%20located%20inside%20a%20coworking%20space%2C%20everything%20shifted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221baa48dd-bc8d-41e9-8879-c3741e4bc8c8%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ETraditional%20day%20care%20never%20worked%20for%20my%20family's%20situation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETraditional%20day%20care%20assumes%20you%20can%20arrive%20by%20a%20specific%20time%20in%20the%20morning.%20They%20typically%20give%20you%20a%20window%2C%20and%20if%20you%20miss%20it%2C%20then%20you're%20out%20of%20luck.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20kind%20of%20set-up%20works%20for%20families%20with%20predictable%20schedules.%20It%20doesn't%20work%20when%20your%20mornings%20are%20spent%20inside%20a%20radio%20station%20or%20when%20your%20workday%20starts%20earlier%20than%20most%20schools%20open.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20didn't%20feel%20fully%20ready%20or%20comfortable%20dropping%20my%202-year-old%20off%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fovernight-daycare-manager-shares-how-it-works-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eday%20care%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20she%20would%20spend%20most%20of%20the%20day%20without%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2273c8189d-cf99-4dd7-8fae-a31a7bd2e8dc%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20coworking%20space%20with%20a%20day%20care%20was%20the%20answer%20I%20needed%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20makes%20this%20model%20work%20for%20us%20is%20flexibility.%20Because%20of%20my%20morning%20radio%20schedule%2C%20we%20don't%20rush%20for%20the%208%20a.m.%20drop-off.%20Instead%2C%20we%20arrive%20after%20lunchtime%20and%20nap%20(2%20p.m.%20to%20be%20exact).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20daughter%20joins%20the%20other%20kids%20for%20the%20afternoon%2C%20where%20she%20learns%20within%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-a-montessori-approach-can-help-give-parents-a-break-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMontessori%20curriculum%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20plays%2C%20and%20socializes%20until%20closing%20at%205%20p.m.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20best%20part%20of%20this%20all%3F%20I%20get%20to%20be%20there%20on-site%2C%20five%20feet%20away%20from%20her%20classroom%3A%20working%2C%20taking%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-zoom-ceo-eric-yuan-runs-calls-meetings-time-background-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EZoom%20calls%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20editing%20audio%2C%20or%20answering%20e-mails.%20That%20alone%20changed%20my%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20no%20longer%20feel%20like%20my%20career%20and%20my%20childcare%20are%20working%20against%20each%20other.%20As%20a%20business%20owner%2C%20this%20setup%20gives%20me%20something%20I%20barely%20had%20before%3A%20carved-out%20time%20to%20get%20work%20done%20while%20my%20child%20is%20cared%20for%20in%20a%20structured%2C%20enriching%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221050%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22a%20corowrking%20space%20with%20couches%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69ab007ffd4fbd083f29a9f5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22752%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20works%20out%20of%20a%20coworking%20space.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Paulina%20Roe%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20not%20squeezing%20work%20into%20nap%20windows%20or%20evenings.%20I'm%20not%20trying%20to%20build%20my%20business%20in%20fragments.%20When%20she's%20in%20school%2C%20I'm%20working%2C%20fully%20present%2C%20focused%2C%20and%20calm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20no%20anxiety%20around%20clock-watching.%20If%20a%20meeting%20runs%20long%20or%20someone%20is%20running%20late%20to%20our%20scheduled%20podcast%20recording%2C%20the%20entire%20day%20doesn't%20get%20off%20track.%20This%20proximity%20creates%20a%20sense%20of%20stability%20I%20didn't%20realize%20I%20was%20missing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cc40007e-6e27-4492-a5e4-f9bc31e2ea2e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EFor%20my%20daughter%2C%20the%20benefits%20are%20just%20as%20meaningful%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20child%20has%20consistency%2C%20peers%20(yay%20to%20friends%20her%20age)%2C%20and%20caregivers%20who%20are%20fully%20focused%20on%20her%20development.%20Her%20day%20isn't%20shaped%20by%20my%20stress%20or%20unpredictability.%20She%20gets%20the%20social%20and%20emotional%20structure%20of%20preschool%20without%20any%20disruption.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20home%2C%20socialization%20was%20a%20large%20missing%20component%20for%20her%2C%20so%20I'm%20grateful%20she%20has%20this%20opportunity%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20isn't%20about%20working%20while%20parenting%20at%20the%20same%20time.%20I'm%20not%20popping%20in%20and%20out%20of%20her%20classroom%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fovershare-work-office-hr-communication-coworkers-employees-gen-z-internet-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eblurring%20boundaries%3C%2Fa%3E.%20If%20anything%2C%20I've%20found%20that%20this%20model%20reinforces%20them.%20When%20she's%20in%20school%2C%20I'm%20getting%20work%20done.%20When%20we're%20together%2C%20I'm%20fully%20present%20with%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2270fb0a19-2f84-4ffd-99b6-c7ed56f6e117%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20live%20an%20unusual%20life%2C%20so%20I%20needed%20an%20unusual%20solution%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20come%20to%20realize%20that%20many%20childcare%20systems%20are%20still%20designed%20around%20a%20workforce%20that%20no%20longer%20exists%3A%20predictable%20hours%2C%20long%20commutes%2C%20and%20a%20default%20parent%20with%20endless%20availability.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20life%20just%20isn't%20built%20like%20that.%20And%20I%20know%20I'm%20not%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECoworking%20preschools%20are%20not%20for%20every%20family.%20They%20don't%20replace%20traditional%20childcare%20or%20solve%20every%20systemic%20issue.%20But%20for%20parents%20like%20me%2C%20other%20remote%20workers%2C%20entrepreneurs%2C%20and%20creatives%2C%20and%20people%20whose%20work%20is%20flexible%20but%20demanding%2C%20they%20provide%20an%20amazing%20option.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20become%20a%20better%20mother%20by%20trying%20harder.%20I%20didn't%20become%20a%20better%20business%20owner%20by%20optimizing%20my%20calendar.%20Once%20my%20childcare%20reflected%20my%20reality%2C%20I%20showed%20up%20calmer%2C%20more%20focused%2C%20and%20present.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20isn't%20childcare%20as%20a%20treat.%20It's%20childcare%20that%20finally%20meets%20working%20parents%20where%20we%20are.%20My%20only%20regret%20is%20that%20I%20didn't%20find%20it%20sooner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmom-work-coworking-space-with-on-site-preschool-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1772885821000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69ab00301fb3fcb426490eff%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmom-work-coworking-space-with-on-site-preschool-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22I%20don't%20have%20a%20regular%20work%20schedule%2C%20so%20I've%20struggled%20with%20childcare%20for%20my%20daughter.%20But%20now%20I%20get%20to%20work%20in%20an%20office%20with%20my%20daughter%20nearby.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Paulina%20Roe)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmom-work-coworking-space-with-on-site-preschool-2026-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Shabana%20Azmi%20says%20she%20will%20ask%20Javed%20Akhtar%20to%20