3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchamath-palihapitiya-spac-investment-critic-daughter-college-fund-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EChamath%20Palihapitiya%20%3C%2Fa%3Esaid%20he%20can't%20believe%20how%20much%20his%20software%20startup%20is%20spending%20on%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20costs%20have%20more%20than%20tripled%20since%20November%20of%2025%2C%26quot%3B%20Palihapitiya%20said%20during%20an%20episode%20of%20the%20%26quot%3BAll-In%20Podcast%26quot%3B%20posted%20on%20Friday.%20%26quot%3BBetween%20the%20inference%20cost%20that%20we%20pay%20AWS%2C%20which%20is%20ginormous%2C%20between%20our%20cost%20with%20Cursor%2C%20between%20Anthropic%2C%20we%20are%20just%20spending%20millions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22youtube%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22strict-origin-when-cross-origin%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FgzwRflcLPAA%3Fstart%3D3363%26feature%3Doembed%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Inside%20the%20Iran%20War%20and%20the%20Pentagon's%20Feud%20with%20Anthropic%20with%20Under%20Secretary%20of%20War%20Emil%20Michael%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EPalihapitiya%20said%208090%2C%20which%20he%20started%20with%20%26quot%3Bthe%20goal%20of%20replacing%2Frewriting%20all%20the%20legacy%20software%20in%20the%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20is%20trending%20toward%20spending%20%2410%20million%20a%20year%20on%20AI%20costs.%20His%20concern%20about%20ballooning%20bills%20comes%20as%20the%20tech%20industry%20continues%20to%20digest%20how%20AI%20is%20upending%20well-established%20fields%20like%20software%20engineering.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20biggest%20fear%20Palihapitiya%20expressed%20is%20that%20while%20AI%20costs%20are%20rising%2C%208090's%20revenues%20are%20not%20increasing%20at%20the%20same%20pace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20problem%20is%20that%20my%20costs%20are%20going%20up%203X%20every%20three%20months%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BMy%20revenues%20are%20not.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20current%20system%2C%20Palihapitiya%20said%20on%20X%2C%20is%20partially%20subsidized%20by%20large%20venture%20capital%20firms%20that%20remain%20some%20of%20the%20biggest%20backers%20of%20AI%20companies%20like%20OpenAI%20and%20Anthropic.%20Some%20in%20tech%20have%20questioned%20the%20sustainability%20of%20the%20current%20approach%2C%20comparing%20it%20to%20how%20Uber%20rides%20were%20first%20cheap%20and%20then%20increased%20in%20cost%20over%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThank%20you%20to%20the%20VCs%20who%20will%20fund%20this%20all-you-can-eat%20token%20consumption%20through%20their%20huge%20investments%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPalihapitiya%20singled%20out%20Cursor%2C%20a%20popular%20AI%20coding%20tool%2C%20as%20a%20source%20of%20some%20of%208090's%20biggest%20AI%20costs.%20He%20said%20that%20Anthropic's%20Claude%20Code%20is%20a%20much%20better%20bargain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20need%20to%20migrate%20off%20of%20Cursor%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote%20on%20X.%20%26quot%3BIts%20just%20too%20expensive%20vs%20Claude%20Code.%20The%20latter%20is%20equivalent%20and%20if%20you%20use%20the%20Pro%20plan%2C%20you%20eliminate%20huge%20Cursor%20bills%20for%20token%20consumption.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConcerns%20about%20rising%20AI%20usage%20bills%20are%20still%20bubbling%20up.%20OpenCode%20creator%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdax-raad-post-ai-coding-workplace-bottleneck-productivity-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EDax%20Raad%3C%2Fa%3E%20recently%20said%20that%20CFOs%20are%20beginning%20to%20wake%20up%20to%20the%20cost%20of%20AI%20bills.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYour%20CFO%20is%20like%20what%20do%20you%20mean%20each%20engineer%20now%20costs%20%242000%20extra%20per%20month%20in%20LLM%20bills%2C%26quot%3B%20Raad%20wrote%20on%20X.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPalihapitiya%20said%20that%20he%20suspects%20some%20of%208090's%20AI%20bills%20might%20be%20due%20to%20Ralph%20loops%2C%20the%20nickname%20for%20a%20usage%20technique%20that%20essentially%20keeps%20feeding%20the%20same%20prompt%20back%20into%20an%20AI%20model%20until%20the%20problem%20is%20solved.%20The%20approach%20is%20named%20after%20%26quot%3BThe%20Simpsons%26quot%3B%20character%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fventurebeat.com%2Ftechnology%2Fhow-ralph-wiggum-went-from-the-simpsons-to-the-biggest-name-in-ai-right-now%3Fref%3Dghuntley.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERalph%20Wiggum%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20beloved%20doofus%20who%20can%20be%20very%20persistent.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEverybody%20has%20gotten%20infatuated%20with%20what%20we%20call%20these%20Ralph%20Wiggum%20loops%2C%20just%20like%20send%20the%20thing%20off%20and%20it'll%20just%20go%20figure%20something%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20Palihapitiya%20said%20during%20the%20podcast.%20%26quot%3BA%2C%20It%20never%20figures%20anything%20out.%20And%20B%2C%20you%20just%20get%20this%20ginormous%20bill%20from%20Cursor.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoing%20forward%2C%20Palihapitiya%20said%20there%20needs%20to%20be%20more%20flexibility%20to%20switch%20between%20models.%20He%20said%20that%20Anthropic's%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpentagon-official-details-how-talks-with-anthropic-fell-apart-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%20recent%20falling%20out%20with%20the%20Pentagon%3C%2Fa%3E%20illustrates%20why%20this%20is%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20need%20to%20gain%20more%20flexibility%20to%20swap%20between%20models%20without%20everything%20breaking%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote%20on%20X.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20this%20is%20both%20a%20cost%20problem%20per%20%231%20but%20its%20also%20a%20strategic%20flexibility%20issue%20after%20the%20events%20between%20Anthropic%20and%20DoW.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fthdxr%2Fstatus%2F20225